			<h2>Real Estate Transactions &amp; Litigation</h2>
			
			<p>Our real estate lawyers handle a broad array of real estate transactions for developers, individuals, cooperatives and condominium associations, banks, credit unions and businesses.</p>
			
			<h4>Among the types of transactions we handle are:</h4>
			
			<ul class="wide">
				<li>Purchases and sales of real estate, including purchase agreements, listing agreements, title searches and opinions, closing statements, tax prorations, seller's affidavits and drafting of deeds, land contracts and related documents.</li>
		   		<li>Mortgages and liens.</li>
		   		<li>Leases, including commercial and residential properties.</li>
		   		<li>Master deeds for condominiums, and related bylaws.</li>
		   		<li>Easements and rights-of-way.</lo>
		   		<li>Construction projects, including preparation of architect, contractor and project manager contracts, notices and liens under the Michigan Construction Lien Act, and insurances, performance bonds and other forms of surety bonds.</li>
			</ul>
			
